    "ops-incident-response": {
      "id": "ops-incident-response",
      "name": "Incident Response",
      "content": "<p>Operational shape of how we respond when something breaks publicly. The detailed SEV ladder and runbooks live in the Legal and Compliance outline — link below.</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-ops",
      "childrenIds": [
        "incident-crosslink-legal",
        "incident-oncall",
        "incident-comms-plan"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "7"
    },
    "incident-crosslink-legal": {
      "id": "incident-crosslink-legal",
      "name": "SEV Ladder + Runbooks (Legal & Compliance)",
      "content": "",
      "type": "outline-link",
      "parentId": "ops-incident-response",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "7.1",
      "linkedOutlineId": "idiampro-legal-compliance"
    },
    "incident-oncall": {
      "id": "incident-oncall",
      "name": "On-Call Rotation",
      "content": "<p><strong>v1: Howard is the rotation.</strong> Every incident routes to him personally, day or night.</p><p><strong>Expansion path.</strong> The first operations or engineering hire takes the primary on-call slot during business hours, with Howard remaining the escalation backstop. As headcount grows to three people, a real rotating on-call schedule kicks in (one-week shifts, primary + backup).</p><p>Until then, the practical implication is that incident readiness is bounded by Howard's availability. The runbook compensates: clear severity tagging and pre-written comms templates mean the response doesn't depend on Howard being fresh.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "ops-incident-response",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "7.2"
    },
    "incident-comms-plan": {
      "id": "incident-comms-plan",
      "name": "Communication Plan",
      "content": "<p>Three audiences for any user-visible incident.</p><ul><li><strong>Status page.</strong> Public-facing page that lists current status, recent incidents, and resolution times. Update within 15 minutes of confirming an incident.</li><li><strong>Email to affected users.</strong> Direct email to anyone impacted: what happened, what we did, what they should do. Plain English, no jargon, no blame-shifting.</li><li><strong>Postmortem.</strong> Within five business days of resolution, publish a postmortem. What happened, why, what we changed to prevent recurrence. Public for major outages, internal-only for minor ones.</li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "ops-incident-response",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "7.3"
    },
    "ops-compliance-privacy": {
      "id": "ops-compliance-privacy",
      "name": "Compliance & Privacy Operations",
      "content": "<p>The day-to-day work of honoring privacy law, AI consent, and data integrity.</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-ops",
      "childrenIds": [
        "comp-data-requests",
        "comp-ai-consent",
        "comp-backup-verification"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "8"
    },
    "comp-data-requests": {
      "id": "comp-data-requests",
      "name": "GDPR / CCPA Data Request Intake",
      "content": "<p>Users in jurisdictions covered by GDPR (EU) or CCPA (California) can request access to, correction of, or deletion of their personal data. The full policy and required disclosures live in the Legal and Compliance outline — link below.</p><p><strong>Operational steps.</strong> Requests come in by email to support@2ndbrainware.com (or the future privacy@ alias). Verify the requester's identity (logged-in confirmation or matching email), then fulfill within the regulatory window (30 days GDPR, 45 days CCPA).</p><p><strong>Privacy details (Legal & Compliance):</strong> see the outline link in the Incident Response section.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "ops-compliance-privacy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "8.1"
    },
    "comp-ai-consent": {
      "id": "comp-ai-consent",
      "name": "AI Consent Reviewer Process",
      "content": "<p>Apple Guideline 5.1.2(i) requires explicit consent before sending user data to third-party AI services. The full process is documented in the AI Data Consent section of the Legal and Compliance outline.</p><p><strong>Operational summary.</strong> Every new AI-driven feature gets a consent review before launch. The reviewer (Howard, with counsel as needed) confirms the consent prompt clearly names the destination provider, the data sent, and the user's ability to revoke.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "ops-compliance-privacy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "8.2"
    },
    "comp-backup-verification": {
      "id": "comp-backup-verification",
      "name": "Backup Verification Cadence",
      "content": "<p>Local outline backups in <code>~/Documents/IDM Outlines/backups/</code> rotate automatically (10 most recent per outline). Verify the rotation is working monthly: open the backups folder, confirm files exist, confirm timestamps are recent.</p><p><strong>Cloud-side backups (when sync is added):</strong> verify the cloud snapshot job runs nightly, log a successful run, and quarterly do a restore-test on a throwaway account to confirm the restore path actually works. A backup is only as good as the last verified restore.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "ops-compliance-privacy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "8.3"
    }
  },
